# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — pigmentation gene-network repo
# Withholds material that CANNOT be redistributed. Redistribution policy and
# per-file rulings: DATA_SOURCES.md ("Redistribution policy") and
# data/raw/papers/REFERENCES.md. This file is deliberately TARGETED, not a
# blanket "*.pdf" — some PDFs (Raghunath CC-BY paper, HIrisPlex webtool manual)
# and the Bajpai Table S1 .xlsx (CC BY via PMC) ARE committed; the Baxter Table S7
# .xlsx is WITHHELD (Wiley subscription, no open copy). See tools/hooks/compliance-allowlist.txt.
# =============================================================================

# --- Publisher full-text articles: cited by DOI, NEVER committed ---
# data/raw/papers/ holds REFERENCES.md only.
data/raw/papers/*
!data/raw/papers/
!data/raw/papers/REFERENCES.md
# 2026-07-12: Kim 2024 (CC BY 4.0) and Zhang 2018 (CC BY-NC 4.0) full-texts + supplements were
# dropped into data/raw/papers/<folder>/ and are ALREADY withheld by the blanket rule above — this is
# the article-PDF convention, NOT a license restriction (both are openly licensed). Also withheld:
# data/raw/papers/wga.pdf = a NIH dbGaP Data Use Certification Agreement (controlled-access legal doc,
# NOT a paper) — recommend deleting it from the repo entirely. If the project USES Kim's or Zhang's
# openly-licensed DATA tables, promote them to their own data/raw/<source>/ folder and clear in
# tools/hooks/compliance-allowlist.txt (Kim CC BY = D'Arcy precedent; Zhang CC BY-NC needs a
# compliance-gate ruling). See DATA_SOURCES.md entries 8-9.

# HIrisPlex-S — Chaitanya 2018 (Elsevier) full text + mmc supplements.
# NOTE: the free Erasmus MC Webtool Manual in the SAME folder IS committed.
data/raw/hirisplexs2018/1-s2.0-S1872497318302205-main.pdf
data/raw/hirisplexs2018/mmc*.pdf

# Bajpai 2023 (Science/AAAS) — Table S1 .xlsx IS committed: the identical data
# table is a supplementary file of the CC BY 4.0 PMC deposit (PMC10901463,
# license_ref=ccbylicense), so the data is redistributable with attribution.
# The typeset article PDF/text is NOT committed.
data/raw/bajpai2023/*.pdf

# Baxter 2018 (Wiley/PCMR) — Table S7 .xlsx is WITHHELD. It is a Version-of-Record
# supplement under Wiley subscription copyright with NO open-license copy
# (PMC10413850 = not Open Access; Crossref license = VOR terms only). Both the
# article PDF and the SI .xlsx are withheld; re-obtain via DOI 10.1111/pcmr.12743
# (see data/raw/papers/REFERENCES.md). The derived CSV in data/processed/ IS committed.
data/raw/baxter2018/*.pdf
data/raw/baxter2018/*.xlsx

# D'Arcy 2023 (MDPI, Bioengineering) — the 6 supplementary .xlsx tables ARE
# committed: the article is Gold Open Access, CC BY 4.0 (DOI 10.3390/bioengineering10010013,
# PMC9854651, PMID 36671585), so the supplement tables are redistributable with
# attribution. Retrieved from Europe PMC (PMC9854651/supplementaryFiles). The
# typeset article PDF/figures are NOT committed (cited by DOI, per the Bajpai precedent).
data/raw/darcy2023/*.pdf

# Walsh 2017 (Springer, Hum Genet) — coefficients source, cited by DOI.
**/walsh2017*.pdf

# --- Local / environment cruft ---
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
.env
# Claude Science / agent local tooling settings — per-machine, not project content.
.claude/

# Internal governance surface — TRACKED and public by default.
# internal/ holds the project's governance documents (project_dashboard.md, TODO.md,
# CHANGELOG.md, START_HERE.md) and the deconvolutor critique reports. These are
# committed so their cross-references resolve on GitHub. Two escape hatches below stay
# private: internal/untracked/ (declutter — move a file there to drop it from the public
# repo without deleting it) and internal/archive/ (retired working docs).

# Declutter escape hatch — anything here is deliberately kept out of the public repo.
internal/untracked/

# 2026-07-13: network×evolution exploration bundle (handoff copy of the
# pigmentation-network-evo-explore side repo). Kept LOCAL only — NOT published to the
# public repo. Hand off by sharing the folder directly. See internal/network-evo-explore/HANDOFF.md.
internal/network-evo-explore/

# Archived documents — retired working docs, renamed with a z_archived_ prefix.
# Standing convention (internal/project_dashboard.md §6): a retired document is renamed
# z_archived_<name> and moved to internal/archive/. These are never committed to the
# public repo. The prefix rule catches any z_archived_ file that lands elsewhere by mistake.
z_archived_*
**/z_archived_*
internal/archive/

# Quarto build artifacts (never commit — CI regenerates)
/_site/
/.quarto/
/_freeze/

# Notebook figure scratch — NB1 savefig()s PNGs here at runtime; the figures that
# ship on the site are the base64 copies embedded IN the notebook (execute: false),
# so these on-disk PNGs are regenerable scratch and are never committed.
/output/

# Sub-agent scratch handoff dirs (not part of the reproducible pipeline)
notebooks/handoff/
handoff/
notebooks/handoff2/

# =============================================================================
# comparative-genomics/ — large genomic data is NOT committed; reproduce it from
# comparative-genomics/config/accessions.tsv (public NCBI accessions). Committed:
# config/, scripts/, envs/environment.yml, results/ summaries. See that dir's README.
# =============================================================================
comparative-genomics/data/
comparative-genomics/**/*.fa
comparative-genomics/**/*.fasta
comparative-genomics/**/*.fna
comparative-genomics/**/*.gff
comparative-genomics/**/*.gff3
comparative-genomics/**/*.bam
comparative-genomics/**/*.bai
comparative-genomics/alignments/
comparative-genomics/**/*.raw.json
